# Hayes Warner

Hayes Warner is a pop singer based in New York City. She was born on July 16, 1999 to an American mother and father. She had breakout success in 2024. Her hits include Predator, Oh! and Zip.
In 2024, she performed at Lollapalooza.
Also in 2024, she released a remake of No Doubt's  “Just a Girl.”
In August 2025, it was revealed that she joined Ryan Murphy’s adaptation of the Bret Easton Ellis novel The Shards for FX as a series regular.
